@node History

History
~~~~~~~
1.0  (1993-06-29) First working version, made for Prof Do Right only.

1.1  (1993-08-04) First public release.

     Added CTRL-C disabling, a version string, and a check for OS V36.

1.2  (1994-04-24) Second public release.

     It doesn't use a tempfile anymore. It reads to memory instead, which
     makes it faster.

     Usage syntax changed! The keyword BACKUP on command line should no
     more be given. The third argument (optional) is taken as backup file.

     The backup file isn't opened unless something will be written to it.
@endnode

